---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = 'ADAS (Advanced Driver Assistance Systems)';
---

<Layout title={title}>
  <main>
    <div class="container fade-in">
      <h1 class="display-6">{title}</h1>
      <p class="lead mb-5">
        Advanced Driver Assistance Systems encompass any driver aids ranging from cameras to crash
        mitigation devices. Some other examples are lane departure warning, blind spot detection,
        pedestrian / bicyclist detection, parking sensors, etc. Most people are not aware that these
        options can be retrofitted in a tasteful and ergonomic way into an existing vehicle, but
        that is what we specialize in.
      </p>
      <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2 row-cols-lg-3 g-4">
        <div class="col">
          <svg
            class="bd-placeholder-img bd-placeholder-img-lg featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto"
            width="500"
            height="500"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            role="img"
            aria-label="Placeholder: 500x500"
            preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice"
            focusable="false"
            ><title>Placeholder</title><rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="#eee"></rect><text
              x="50%"
              y="50%"
              fill="#aaa"
              dy=".3em">500x500</text
            >
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
